  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Assessment of health-related quality of life in COPD patients with severe chronic respiratory
      failure requires appropriate and highly specific measurement tools. We attempt to validate
      the Chinese version of the Severe Respiratory Insufficiency Questionnaire (SRI)
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
